Asher Public School would like to announce the following the Asher FFA Annual Pig Roast & Pie Auction will be held on September 17 starting @ 6:30 pm. The event will be held outside in front of the High School building.

* We ask that everyone observe social distancing guidelines of staying at least 6 feet apart during the event.

*Hand washing stations will be available at the event.

* If you are not feeling well PLEASE STAY AT HOME.

Thank you for your help during this challenging time.

post_text:
Dear parents and students,

There are many more dangers that children/teenagers face online every day. The Internet can be a fun and interactive space, but there are safety precautions to take. There are so many different social media apps and most have different ways of communication.

It is easy to add strangers, or let them ‚Äúfollow‚Äù you and then that person can see personal information, and maybe even your location. The more a person interacts online or posts videos, the more likely they will receive some kind of interaction with a stranger.

All phones are different with how location services work. Be aware that each app has their own location preferences. Please be careful of what you‚Ä¶

post_text:
Due to the situation at hand with COVID-19 parents, guardians and visitors will not be allowed inside the school buildings at this time. If you feel the need to bring your child(ren) things to the school you will need to come to the north entrance and ring the door buzzer and someone will meet you at the door to gather the items for your child(ren).

If you need to pick up your child before the end of the day again, come to the north entrance and ring the door buzzer and we will bring your child(ren) out to you. If you are dropping them off late they need to come to the north entrance and check in at the office before going to class.

First day of school Pre-k and Kindergarten parents (ONLY) will be allowed in the South entrance straight to the classroom to drop off student. You MUST have on a mask and allowed to stay 15 minuets max. After Thursday you will no longer be allowed to enter the building.

No adults except for teachers and school staff are to enter the Elementary building at any time.

We thank you for understanding and helping with the matter at hand.

Bozho (hello)
The COVID-19 Technology Program offers a $400 allowance to equip all CPN K-12 children ages 5-18 with technology tools, such as laptops and internet access, that will better enable distance learning necessitated by COVID-19.
For high school students ages 14 - 18, the COVID-19 ACT/SAT Online Workshop Program will provide eligible CPN tribal members with the opportunity to receive a $40, one-time reimbursement payment for ACT/SAT online prep fees. If you are interested in learning about ACT/SAT preparation programs that our department recommends, please feel free to reach out to the CPN Department of Education at college@potawatomi.org or 405-695-6028.

shared_text:
Citizen Potawatomi Nation
June 9 at 8:00 AM ¬∑

The Native Learning Center is hosting a poster contest for ages 5 to 18! The theme is "What Homes Means to Me," and they are accepting entries through June 30. Age brackets are 5-10, 11-13, and 14-18 with winners in each one.

All tribal communities are welcome to submit! Posters must be original works of art. Acceptable mediums include markers, paint, crayons, colored pencils, beads and fabric! While all forms of art are welcome, all submissions must be poster friendly. Get as creative as you'd like! Create a poster that shows what home means to you!

Once you've finished your poster or if you have any questions, submit to: WilmaNoah@semtribe.com or KrystalCedeno@semtribe.com.

post_text: Tuesday, March 24th reminder about our food program! Lot's yesterday didn't want to come for fear of taking from those who really need it. This program is funded by the state it IS for ALL children ages 18 and under. It is not judged by income or who needs it the most. Each child will recieve 2 meals and 2 milks. The better the turn out we have the better it is for our counts. Please make the trip today, if you have families close to you who can't make it please let us know! Remember 10 am to 12 pm south end doors! Pull up we will bring to you. Please, STAY IN YOUR VEHICLE! Thank you.

shared_text:
Oklahoma Youth Expo
March 23 at 11:16 AM ¬∑

With the cancelation of OYE, it put many of our exhibitors in a financial hardship. We are dedicated for our exhibitors and the families of OYE and have since had many sponsors come forward to help those in need. We are very excited to announce the 2020 Financial Hardship Scholarship, which is available to senior market animal exhibitors who did not receive a 2020 OYE Academic Scholarship. Thanks to the generosity of many of our sponsors, we will award 100, $1,000 scholarships to seniors who are preparing to pursue their higher education goals. Applications are due April 10th.

An application can be found here: https://okyouthexpo.com/scholarships/scholarship-applications/

Asher Public Schools
March 20 at 9:24 AM ¬∑

March 20, 2020

With Asher Public Schools closed until April 6th, per a state ordered closure, we realize these are very trying times for our state and community. Beginning Monday, March 23, 2020 we will provide two meals per day to our student community. Anyone 18 and under is eligible for the meals. These meals will be a grab and go available from 10 AM to 12 PM on the south end of main building (Hamilton Building). Please, do not enter the building someone will bring meals to your car.

To ensure we are being proactive to address this impending threat, tough decisions are having to be made everywhere, and the same goes for us in the FFA world. No easy way to break the news. State FFA Interscholastics for all non-national qualifying CDE/LDE events for 2020 will be canceled. This includes the following:

post_text:
PSA!
Please remember it is still Flu season.. if your child is not feeling well or has ran fever less than 24 hours before the school day, please keep them home!!

It is policy a child has to be fever free without medication for 24 hours before returning to school. Also, if they have a Dr. Note please make sure they do not return before the date the Dr. has stated on the note.

This is to prevent an outbreak to other students and our staff.

Please be courteous of others during this time of year.

Thank you!

We have had a family in our community that have lost their home this morning in an early morning fire. Everyone is OK, but they have lost everything. They had no insurance. We are taking up donations of any kind to help this family. If you would like to donate clothes, household items or money, please bring it to the school office. Also, please include this family in your daily prayer to help them through this hard time.

There are 2 adults and 3 family dogs

Man sizes:
XL shirts, 30x34 jeans, Med. underware, size 10 shoes and socks.

Woman sizes: she is 7 months pregnant please keep in mind
Med. - Lg. pants maternity
L-XL shirts maternity
size 7 underware
shoes size 8

Everything neutral for baby, diapers, wipes
Please NO Johnson & Johnson products.

dogfood any variety hard food.
med to large kennels ( she lost 3 )

We THANK YOU and so does the family. Any donation big or small will help tremendously.

shared_text:
Oklahoma Hall of Fame at the Gaylord-Pickens Museum
August 18, 2019 at 1:00 PM ¬∑

The deadline to apply for the 2019 Oklahoma Hall of Fame Scholarship is quickly approaching! If you're an Oklahoma high school senior (or if you have one at home), don't miss this chance to earn $6,000.

The winning student will be selected based on leadership roles, civic/community involvement, academic achievement and knowledge of our great state. Students MUST commit to attending an Oklahoma college or university to be considered. Here's the kicker ‚Äî you can't nominate yourself, and you can't nominate your kids. All nominations need to be made by teachers, administrators or adults not related to the student.

Visit oklahomahof.com/scholarships to download the nomination form.
